&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6 Neurosciences&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rotational Occupational Therapist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for a motivated and experienced Occupational Therapist (OT) to join our dynamic Neurosciences Occupational Therapy team at the Royal Free London NHS Foundation Trust. The post includes 9 month rotations across the following areas:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Acute Neurosciences – Royal Free Hospital, Hampstead.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complex Management Team – Royal Free Hospital, Hampstead&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inpatient Neuro-rehabilitation – Royal Free Neurological Rehabilitation Centre, Edgware Community Hospital.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Community Neurological Conditions Management Team – Royal Free Neurological Rehabilitation Centre, Edgware Community Hospital.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Critical Care, HDU, Royal Free Hospital, Hampstead.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be joining an established Neurosciences Therapy Team and will have the opportunity to develop specialist skills in the assessment and treatment of acute and chronic neuro-disability patients. You will be working as part of a specialist Neurosciences multidisciplinary team and will be involved in therapy in-service training, education and service development. You will be encouraged to participate in clinical governance and quality improvement activities within the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must have previous experience in the field of Neurosciences and be able to demonstrate their knowledge and skills in neurological assessment and treatment planning. Excellent communication skills, a solution-focussed approach and a commitment to continuing professional development are essential to this position.&lt;/p&gt;
